  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "It is important to note, that even with the reduced evaluation caused by providing the label for GPT reappraisal, GPT was still rated higher in effectiveness compared to both the human reappraisals with label (b = 0.48, t(109) = 2.52, p =.013, R 2 = 0.04, 95% CI [0.10, 0.85]) human reappraisals without label (b = 0.42, t(133) = 2.09, p =.038, R 2 = 0.04, 95% CI [0.02, 0.81]).",
    "Regarding empathy of reappraisals, we did not find a significant interaction between source and label, although results were in the same direction as effectiveness (interaction: b = -0.12, t(",
    "= -1.87, p =.062, R 2 = 0.04, 95% CI [-0.24,0.01]; label difference GPT: b = -0.138, t(1499) = -1.57, p =.117, 95% CI [-0.31, 0.04]; label difference human: b =-0.02, t(501) =-0.30, p =.769, R 2 = 0.04, 95%",
    "CI [-0.15, 0.11]).",
    "We did, however, find a significant interaction in evaluation of novelty (b =-0.13, t(24238) = -2.18, p =.029, R 2 = 0.03, 95% CI [-0.24,-0.01]) and a significant difference between the label and no label condition for GPT (b = -0.25, t(1187) = 2.77, p =.006, R 2 = 0.03, 95% CI = [0.07, 0.42]), but not for reappraisals produced by humans (b =-0.12, t(499) = -1.67, p =.095, R 2 = 0.03, 95% CI [-0.02, 0.26])."
  ],
